<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="67" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1440,255,2020]" box="[151,1055,255,279]" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,255,279]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tennessen" authorityYear="2011" box="[405,507,256,279]" class="Insecta" family="Gomphidae" genus="Perigomphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis box="[405,507,256,279]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="67">angularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the basal, dorso-medial angle of the cerci.
</paragraph>
